CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 7, 1957, pg.1 reads: "Rosella Bush Retires After Carrying Mail for 40 Years - Handy With Tools - For a long time, Rosella Bush has been proving to astonished friends and neighbors that she is handy with tools. She does most of the carpentry, masonry and electrical work on the seven houses she owns.  Here she is trying out the new power saw which she purchased as "A present to myself," following her retirement, last week. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Rosella Bush wearing light colored hat, eyeglasses, and plaid shirt, using electric circular saw to cut lumber, standing on lawn with trees
